WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:05.242
Previously on Mars.

00:06.121 --> 00:07.492
We knew Mars wouldn't welcome us

00:07.492 --> 00:09.621
with open arms.

00:09.621 --> 00:12.332
Warning, systems offline.

00:15.952 --> 00:17.952
Permission to
switch from primary to backup.

00:17.952 --> 00:19.742
Do it.

00:19.742 --> 00:22.032
Prepare for retropropulsion.

00:23.371 --> 00:26.532
We were ready to
give everything to get there.

00:27.911 --> 00:29.821
Mission Control,
this is Daedalus,

00:29.821 --> 00:31.492
we're looking at a red planet.

00:33.582 --> 00:35.371
And we knew
we'd have to fight even harder

00:35.371 --> 00:36.701
if we wanted to stay.

00:36.701 --> 00:38.332
How far did we overshoot?

00:38.332 --> 00:41.451
75.3 kilometers.

00:41.451 --> 00:43.491
Mission
Control confirmed the rover

00:43.491 --> 00:46.161
is 2,000 kilos over
maximum payload.

00:46.161 --> 00:48.621
The odds are we won't make it.

00:48.621 --> 00:50.332
But no matter what happened,

00:50.332 --> 00:53.371
we'd do everything we could
to make the workshop module

00:53.371 --> 00:56.031
our new basecamp.

00:56.031 --> 00:58.661
Because the thing
that kept us pushing,

00:58.661 --> 01:02.371
it wasn't just inside us.

01:04.950 --> 01:07.621
Our species has always
been driven to build beyond

01:07.621 --> 01:11.162
what we know.

01:11.162 --> 01:15.912
We migrated across all of earth.

01:15.912 --> 01:20.581
Created settlements,
constructed cities,

01:20.581 --> 01:24.031
and when we finally
left our home planet,

01:24.031 --> 01:26.531
we knew the risks involved.

01:26.531 --> 01:29.162
As we set sail,

01:29.162 --> 01:34.912
we ask God's blessing
on the most hazardous and

01:34.912 --> 01:38.371
dangerous and greatest
adventure on which

01:38.412 --> 01:42.741
man has ever embarked.

01:42.741 --> 01:47.912
However will
is a double edged sword.

01:48.871 --> 01:51.281
Again, and again it's taken
us farther than we ever

01:51.281 --> 01:53.991
thought we could go.

01:53.991 --> 01:57.371
But this time we had seized
on an object so vast,

01:57.371 --> 02:01.662
so difficult to attain.

02:01.662 --> 02:03.201
I couldn't help but
wonder if we might have

02:03.201 --> 02:06.121
finally pushed too far.

